g.text: WHERE Clause Bytecode Execution | age > 18 AND status = 'active'
Why inverted? Early rejection is more efficient. Jump to SKIP immediately when predicate fails. No need to track 'and' success - fall through to output.
Loop to next row without output
Advance cursor, check for more rows
Le r1(18), r3(25), 8 - 25 <= 18? FALSE - continue (no jump)
Ne r2('active'), r4('active'), 8 - 'active' != 'active'? FALSE - continue (no jump)
Le r1(18), r3(15), 8 - 15 <= 18? TRUE - JUMP to 8 (SKIP)
Le r1(18), r3(30), 8 - 30 <= 18? FALSE - continue (no jump)
Ne r2('active'), r4('inactive'), 8 - 'active' != 'inactive'? TRUE - JUMP to 8 (SKIP)
